1 such violation may shall, in addition to any other fine or penalty,
2 be assessed a fee in an the amount not exceeding One Thousand
3 Dollars ($1,000.00) of Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00) to be
4 deposited in the Motorcycle Safety and Education Program Revolving
5 Fund established in Section 40-123 of this title. Any person
6 convicted of failure to yield a right-of-way and who causes a
7 serious bodily injury as a result of such violation may, in addition
8 to any other fine or penalty, be assessed a fee in the amount of
9 Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00) to be deposited in the Motorcycle
10 Safety and Education Program Revolving Fund. For the purposes of
11 this section, a serious bodily injury is an injury that is serious
12 in nature but does not quite rise to the level of injury of great
13 bodily injury or a fatality.
14 The monies deposited as provided in this section subsection
15 shall be used to promote public awareness of the dangers of driving
16 while under the influence of alcohol or any controlled substance and
17 to promote motorcycle safety and defensive driving for youth.
18 B. In addition to the fee provided in subsection A of this
19 section, the court may impose additional penalties, including:
20 1. A remedial driving course;
21 2. A loss of driver license for ninety (90) days; or
22 3. A payment of restitution of no less than Three Thousand
23 Dollars ($3,000.00), but no more than Ten Thousand Dollars
24 ($10,000.00).
